The paper deals with algorithms for the classic matroid intersection problem, which is a fundamental problem in combinatorial optimization and has applications in various fields such as network design and scheduling. The paper presents algorithms for both the independence oracle and rank oracle settings, which are common in matroid theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
